\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_8419999\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_8419999\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 29, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gbf1665702906922.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gbf1665702906922.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gbf1665702906922.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gbf1665702906922\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                                 \n Sign Certification Requests\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Certificates need to be signed by an internal or external certificate authority.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__context_w5119ab1b5b1_w5120ab1b5_w5121ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__topic_d39746e1_d39747e1_d39748e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__p_d39749e1_d39750e1_d39751e1\">If your organization acts as its own Certificate Authority, someone must be authorized to sign certification requests from employees that need a certificate for their secure connection.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__li_d19961e1_d19962e1_d19963e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__p_d39752e1_d39753e1_d39754e1\">The requestor generates a key for the\n               certificate. For example:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">openssl genrsa -aes256 -out cert.key 2048</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__li_d19964e1_d19965e1_d19966e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__p_d39755e1_d39756e1_d39757e1\">The requestor generates a certificate signing\n               request. For example: </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">openssl req -config openssl.cnf /\n -key cert.key /\n -new -sha256 /\n -out cert.csr</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">The <span class=\"ph filepath\">openssl.cnf</span>configuration file is a default configuration\n                  file that provides basic information about the certificate owner.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__li_d19967e1_d19968e1_d19969e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__p_d39758e1_d39759e1_d39760e1\">The company Certificate Authority signs the\n               request:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">It is important to know whether the certificate is for a TLS server or a TLS\n                  client.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__p_d39761e1_d39762e1_d39763e1\">In case of a TLS server:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">openssl ca -config ca_intermediate.cnf /\n -extensions server_cert /\n -days 375 -notext -md sha256 /\n -in cert.csr /\n -out cert.crt</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__p_d39764e1_d39765e1_d39766e1\">In case of a TLS client:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">openssl ca -config ca_intermediate.cnf /\n -extensions usr_cert /\n -days 375 -notext -md sha256 /\n -in cert.csr /\n -out cert.crt</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__li_d19970e1_d19971e1_d19972e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">The company Certificate Authority verifies the certificate. For example:\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">openssl x509 -noout -text -in cert.crt</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__result_w5122ab1b5b5_w5123ab1b5_w5124ab1\">\n<div class=\"sectiondiv result\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__topic_d39767e1_d39768e1_d39769e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__p_d39770e1_d39771e1_d39772e1\">The certificate is now signed and can be sent back to the requestor.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"sectiondiv postreq\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__topic_d39773e1_d39774e1_d39775e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gbf1665702906922__p_d39776e1_d39777e1_d39778e1\">The root CA certificate and the intermediate certificate (not their keys!) must be made available in the trust store or concatenated as a single CA certificate file on the machine that will do the verification.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8419999\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8419999\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Sign Certification Requests Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 29, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Sign Certification Requests Certificates need to be signed by an internal or external certificate authority. If your organization acts as its own Certificate Authority, someone must be authorized to sign certification requests from employees that need a certificate for their secure connection. The requestor generates a key for the certificate. For example: openssl genrsa -aes256 -out cert.key 2048 Copy The requestor generates a certificate signing request. For example: openssl req -config openssl.cnf / -key cert.key / -new -sha256 / -out cert.csr Copy The openssl.cnf configuration file is a default configuration file that provides basic information about the certificate owner. The company Certificate Authority signs the request: It is important to know whether the certificate is for a TLS server or a TLS client. In case of a TLS server: openssl ca -config ca_intermediate.cnf / -extensions server_cert / -days 375 -notext -md sha256 / -in cert.csr / -out cert.crt Copy In case of a TLS client: openssl ca -config ca_intermediate.cnf / -extensions usr_cert / -days 375 -notext -md sha256 / -in cert.csr / -out cert.crt Copy The company Certificate Authority verifies the certificate. For example: openssl x509 -noout -text -in cert.crt Copy The certificate is now signed and can be sent back to the requestor. The root CA certificate and the intermediate certificate (not their keys!) must be made available in the trust store or concatenated as a single CA certificate file on the machine that will do the verification. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}